In the diagram, classes are represented with boxes that contain three compartments: The <font color="#ff0000">top compartment</font> contains the name of the class. It is printed in bold and centered, and the first letter is capitalized. The <font color="#ff0000">middle compartment</font> contains the attributes of the class. They are left-aligned and the first letter is lowercase. The <font color="#ff0000">bottom compartment</font> contains the operations the class can execute. They are also left-aligned and the first letter is lowercase.
